festival.introText:
Wide Awake is an independent festival for music fans looking for something different.

Expect leftfield Indie, Post Punk, Electronica, Techno, Jazz and more from an array of artists you won’t find anywhere else at the same festival in London.

Brought to you by Bad Vibrations, LNZRT and Snap Crackle & Pop, some of the original Field Day and Dimensions festivals founders and the people behind MOTH CLUB, The Shacklewell Arms, The Waiting Room, Peckham Audio and Test Pressing Festival, Wide Awake’s a party for people who care… about music and more.
festival.descriptionText: Get more information about Wide Awake 2023 including festival tickets, news, reviews and lineups.

faqs.question: When is Wide Awake 2023?
faqs.answer: Wide Awake takes place on Saturday 27th May 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to Wide Awake?
faqs.answer:
Address: Brockwell Park, Norwood Rd, London SE24 9BJ

Closest Train Station: Herne Hill

Closest Tube: Brixton

Buses: 3, 68, 196, 201, 322, 468, 690, N3, N68

faqs.question: Where is Wide Awake?
faqs.answer: Wide Awake is held at Brockwell Park, Norwood Rd, London SE24 9BJ.

faqs.question: Does Wide Awake have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Wide Awake. You may be asked to show photo ID. A Challenge 25 policy will be in operation at all bars.

faqs.question: Can I bring food & drink into Wide Awake?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Wide Awake. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival, serving up organic, vegetarian and vegan options. Free drinking water will also be available - please feel free to bring a re-useable water bottle.

faqs.question: What can I not bring to Wide Awake?
faqs.answer:
• Drones
  • Drugs / Controlled substances including "legal highs" and Nitrous Oxide
  • Filming equipment
  • Loose glitter
  • Liquids other than sealed bottles of water up to 500ml or sun cream and hand sanitiser up to 50ml.
  • Glass in any form (including perfume bottles)
  • Cans or metal containers
  • Spray cans, Gas cannisters or compressed gas in any container
  • Fireworks, flares, smoke cannisters, Chinese lanterns
  • Camping stoves or cooking apparatus, explosives
  • Hand held communication devices such as radios, radio jammers / scanners
  • Firearms, knives or blades, replica weapons of any sort
  • Umbrellas including large golf umbrellas
  • Balloons
  • Stools / camping sticks / chairs or other furniture
  • Gazebos or parasols
  • Sports equipment
  • Flags and banners
  • Megaphones, amplification equipment
  • Klaxons, airhorns or other similar items capable of making loud noise
  • Laser pens
  • Scooters, skateboards, bicycles, trolleys, buggies 
  • Any other item which security may deem hazardous
